name: School for International Training/World Learning
directions: SIT has multiple All Gender Restrooms that are available to SIT Students, Staff, and Faculty. There are three All Gender Restrooms in the Student Center in the 1st floor lobby area, one of which is ADA accessible. The Rotch Building has one ADA accessible All Gender Restroom on the 1st floor in the building's lobby. The Lowey International Center has two All Gender Restrooms, both of which are ADA accessible. One is at the end of the 1st floor hallway, past the dining room, just outside of room 101. The other All Gender Restroom is located on the same hallway, and has an ADA accessible shower available for student, staff, and faculty use. The Sandanona Graduate Center has two All Gender Restrooms which are ADA accessible, one is located on the 1st floor, and the other on the 2nd floor. Each of these restrooms are labeled with braille "All Gender Restroom" signs. Additionally, the Boyce building, Graduate building, Bliss House, Dickinson Annex, Kipling Cottage, and Upton building all have single use gender neutral restrooms located on each floor, although these restrooms are not labeled.
comment: SIT is a private campus for use by SIT Students, Staff, and Faculty. If you would like to visit campus, please check in with the Admissions Office in the Graduate Building.
